        "text": "## Result\n\n| Ligand Class | Total Count |\n|---|---|\n| Amino Acids | **297** |\n\nThere are **297 ligands** classified under the \"Amino Acids\" class in the NIST SRD-46 (Critically Selected Stability Constants of Metal Complexes) database.\n\nThis is a substantial collection, reflecting the importance of amino acids in coordination chemistry — they are versatile ligands that can coordinate metals through their amine (–NH₂), carboxylate (–COO⁻), and various side-chain donor groups, making them relevant to bioinorganic chemistry, nutrition, and environmental science.\n\n*Source: NIST Standard Reference Database 46*",
